linkedlist

Interface LinkedList<T>

  • Type Parameters:
    T -
    All Superinterfaces:
    java.lang.Iterable<T>, LinkedListKernel<T>, Standard<LinkedList<T>>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    LinkedListSecondary, SinglyLinkedList

    public interface LinkedList<T>
extends LinkedListKernel<T>, java.lang.Iterable<T>
    Additional functionality upon the bare-bones functionality afforded by the SinglyLinkedListKernel interface. All method implementations must, by design, use only the SinglyLinkedListKernel methods to perform operations on the component.
    Author:
    Matthew Shoemaker

        Ensures:

      • moveToPosition

        void moveToPosition(int pos)
        Shifts the focus of this to the (pos + 1)th element in this. A linked list has no index value, but this can be essentially thought of as an index value in the most simple terms.
        Parameters:
        pos - position to which the focus will shift
        Requires:
        pos < this.length and 0 <= pos
        Ensures:
        this.position = pos
